benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: Successful update of bundle external key is tested (TC01, TC14, etc.).
Partial Update: Tests for missing body, missing externalKey, malformed JSON ensure partial updates are rejected (TC06, TC08, TC07).
Non-Existing Resource: Tests for malformed and non-existent bundleId (TC03, TC04, TC15).
Authentication & Authorization: Unauthorized and missing token scenarios (TC12).
Edge Cases: Long key, empty key, special characters, spaces, extra fields (TC10, TC11, TC19, TC20, TC21).
Performance: Large payload and response time (TC16, TC23).
gaps: GET Method guidelines (Valid Request, Empty Response, Pagination, Query Parameters, Authorization, Rate Limiting, Caching Behavior) are not covered.
POST Method guidelines (Valid Payload, Invalid Payload, Duplicate Submission, Large Payloads, Validation, Server Error Handling) are not covered.
PATCH Method guidelines (Partial Update, Invalid Data Types, Concurrency Issues) are not covered.
DELETE Method guidelines (Valid Deletion, Non-Existent Resource, Concurrency, Soft Deletes) are not covered.
recommendations: Add tests for GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE guidelines if those endpoints are part of the system.
Consider adding rate limiting and caching behavior tests for GET endpoints.
Include tests for duplicate submissions and large payload handling for POST if applicable.
Add tests for soft delete behavior if DELETE is used.
Ensure that all error codes and edge cases are documented in the API spec.
